                                  INTRODUCTION:


This is a very strong monitor that allow you to debug your programs.
Remember that this program DON'T use systems routine, than it isn't
100% stable and than it will CRASH your AMIGA in any time!!!
To active GigaMonitor you have to press HELP key;

     NEVER active GigaMonitor while your I/O DEVICES are working!!!!!!
     -----------------------------------------------------------------

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>  USE THIS PROGRAM ON YOUR OWN RISK  <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

You can copy this program to your friends but you have to include this
documentation, furthermore you MUST NOT to change any part of the program and
documentation.

-----------------------------

GIGAMONITOR commands:

d              MC 68000 disassembler                             - d(address)
m              Show/edit memory as bytes                         - m address
n              Show/edit memory as ASCII                         - n address
x              exit                                              - x
r              Show/edit processor registers                     - r(reg value)
destroy        exit and destroy GigaMonitor                      - destroy
unfreeze       Try to unfreeze diskdrives if you have stopped
               them activing GigaMonitor while they were working - unfreeze

-----------------------------

GIGAMONITOR key commands:

TAB            insert spaces
ESC            escape any command
F1             CLR + cursor home
F6             cursor priority over bitplanes
SH F6          bitplanes priority over cursor
F10            Switch screen
POWER-LED is off = ready to execute commands!
Use cursorkeys in combination with shift too
